    "updated_at": "2026-01-01T13:16:56Z",
    "body": "I noticed you're loading both Powerline and starship in your `.zshrc`:\n\n```bash\nsource /usr/share/powerline/bindings/zsh/powerline.zsh\neval \"$(starship init zsh)\"\n```\n\nBoth tools register a `zle-keymap-select` widget that calls `zle reset-prompt` on vi mode change. When starship wraps the existing widget, `zle reset-prompt` ends up being called twice, which likely causes the display corruption.\n\nCould you try commenting out the Powerline line and see if the issue persists? Since both are prompt themes, they're not really meant to be used together.",
